{'problem_id': 'op_000035', 'moved_to': 'solved', 'target_row': {'id': 'op_000035', 'stmt': '∀ Γ A, AtomicCtx Γ → ((LeftRep Γ A ∨ RightRep Γ A) ↔ (Γ ⇒ A ∧ every division connective occurring in A has the same orientation))', 'src': 'expand', 'mode': 'expand_candidate', 'summary_delta': 'The proof logs show that the solved witness fails fragment representability exactly because its succedent mixes both slash directions. Making that into an iff would give an exact interface theorem: on atomic contexts, one-sided fragments capture precisely the full derivable sequents with one-sided succedent shape. That is a sharp structural boundary, not another isolated negative example.', 'source_kind': 'expand_candidate', 'generated_from_source_id': 'op_000025', 'generated_from_source_kind': 'open_problem', 'priority': 'high', 'priority_rationale': 'Exact iff fragment boundary for atomic contexts; it would turn the current gap witness into a genuine separation/classification theorem.', 'failure_count': 0, 'parent_problem_ids': []}, 'solved_row': {'id': 'op_000035', 'stmt': '∀ Γ A, AtomicCtx Γ → ((LeftRep Γ A ∨ RightRep Γ A) ↔ (Γ ⇒ A ∧ every division connective occurring in A has the same orientation))', 'thm': 'thm_atomic_context_one_sided_iff_000035', 'run_id': '20260413-173137-loop', 'iteration': 19, 'session_type': 'loop'}, 'counterexample_row': None, 'duplicate_stmt_rows_removed': [], 'current_iteration': 19, 'picked_problem_id': 'op_000035', 'picked_problem_priority': 'high', 'result': 'proof', 'verify_success': True, 'verify_error_excerpt': '', 'original_stmt': '∀ Γ A, AtomicCtx Γ → ((LeftRep Γ A ∨ RightRep Γ A) ↔ (Γ ⇒ A ∧ every division connective occurring in A has the same orientation))', 'statement_prelude_code': 'def LeftDivisionOnly : Tp → Prop\n  | Tp.atom _ => True\n  | Tp.ldiv A B => LeftDivisionOnly A ∧ LeftDivisionOnly B\n  | Tp.rdiv _ _ => False\n\ndef RightDivisionOnly : Tp → Prop\n  | Tp.atom _ => True\n  | Tp.ldiv _ _ => False\n  | Tp.rdiv A B => RightDivisionOnly A ∧ RightDivisionOnly B\n\nabbrev SameDivisionOrientation (A : Tp) : Prop :=\n  LeftDivisionOnly A ∨ RightDivisionOnly A', 'formalized_stmt': '∀ (Γ : List Tp) (A : Tp), AtomicCtx Γ → ((LeftRep Γ A ∨ RightRep Γ A) ↔ (Γ ⇒ A ∧ SameDivisionOrientation A))', 'prelude_code': "def LeftDivisionOnly : Tp → Prop\n  | Tp.atom _ => True\n  | Tp.ldiv A B => LeftDivisionOnly A ∧ LeftDivisionOnly B\n  | Tp.rdiv _ _ => False\n\ndef RightDivisionOnly : Tp → Prop\n  | Tp.atom _ => True\n  | Tp.ldiv _ _ => False\n  | Tp.rdiv A B => RightDivisionOnly A ∧ RightDivisionOnly B\n\nabbrev SameDivisionOrientation (A : Tp) : Prop :=\n  LeftDivisionOnly A ∨ RightDivisionOnly A\n\nlemma left_only_of_left_tp (A : Left.Tp) : LeftDivisionOnly A.toProductFree := by\n  induction A with\n  | atom s =>\n      trivial\n  | ldiv A B ihA ihB =>\n      exact ⟨ihA, ihB⟩\n\nlemma right_only_of_right_tp (A : Right.Tp) : RightDivisionOnly A.toProductFree := by\n  induction A with\n  | atom s =>\n      trivial\n  | rdiv B A ihB ihA =>\n      exact ⟨ihB, ihA⟩\n\nlemma exists_left_tp_of_left_only {A : Tp} (hA : LeftDivisionOnly A) :\n    ∃ A' : Left.Tp, A'.toProductFree = A := by\n  induction A with\n  | atom s => exact ⟨Left.Tp.atom s, rfl⟩\n  | ldiv A B ihA ihB =>\n      rcases hA with ⟨hA, hB⟩\n      rcases ihA hA with ⟨A', rfl⟩\n      rcases ihB hB with ⟨B', rfl⟩\n      exact ⟨Left.Tp.ldiv A' B', rfl⟩\n  | rdiv A B =>\n      cases hA\n\nlemma exists_right_tp_of_right_only {A : Tp} (hA : RightDivisionOnly A) :\n    ∃ A' : Right.Tp, A'.toProductFree = A := by\n  induction A with\n  | atom s => exact ⟨Right.Tp.atom s, rfl⟩\n  | ldiv A B =>\n      cases hA\n  | rdiv B A ihB ihA =>\n      rcases hA with ⟨hB, hA⟩\n      rcases ihB hB with ⟨B', rfl⟩\n      rcases ihA hA with ⟨A', rfl⟩\n      exact ⟨Right.Tp.rdiv B' A', rfl⟩\n\nlemma exists_left_ctx_of_atomic (Γ : List Tp) (hΓ : AtomicCtx Γ) :\n    ∃ Γ' : List Left.Tp, Left.ctxToProductFree Γ' = Γ := by\n  induction Γ with\n  | nil =>\n      exact ⟨[], rfl⟩\n  | cons A Γ ih =>\n      have hA : is_atom A := hΓ A (by simp)\n      have htail : AtomicCtx Γ := by\n        intro x hx\n        exact hΓ x (by simp [hx])\n      rcases ih htail with ⟨Γ', hΓ'⟩\n      cases A with\n      | atom s =>\n          refine ⟨Left.Tp.atom s :: Γ', ?_⟩\n          simp [Left.ctxToProductFree]\n          exact ⟨rfl, hΓ'⟩\n      | ldiv A B =>\n          cases hA\n      | rdiv A B =>\n          cases hA\n\nlemma exists_right_ctx_of_atomic (Γ : List Tp) (hΓ : AtomicCtx Γ) :\n    ∃ Γ' : List Right.Tp, Right.ctxToProductFree Γ' = Γ := by\n  induction Γ with\n  | nil =>\n      exact ⟨[], rfl⟩\n  | cons A Γ ih =>\n      have hA : is_atom A := hΓ A (by simp)\n      have htail : AtomicCtx Γ := by\n        intro x hx\n        exact hΓ x (by simp [hx])\n      rcases ih htail with ⟨Γ', hΓ'⟩\n      cases A with\n      | atom s =>\n          refine ⟨Right.Tp.atom s :: Γ', ?_⟩\n          simp [Right.ctxToProductFree]\n          exact ⟨rfl, hΓ'⟩\n      | ldiv A B =>\n          cases hA\n      | rdiv A B =>\n          cases hA", 'prover_statement_result': 'ok', 'prover_attempts_used': 1, 'priority_refresh_ran': True, 'priority_refresh_error': '', 'expand_candidates': [{'statement': 'Characterize exactly those sequents `Γ ⇒ A` for which every formula in `Γ` together with `A` has one common division orientation, and prove that on precisely this class the full calculus and the corresponding one-sided fragment have the same derivable sequents.', 'rationale': 'The solved theorem gives this equivalence only for atomic contexts, where fragment preimages are automatic. Extending it to the exact common-orientation regime would identify the real boundary at which the full Lambek calculus collapses to a one-sided subsystem, turning the current atomic-context interface into a genuine structural classification rather than a special-case transport lemma.'}, {'statement': 'Prove that a derivable sequent `Γ ⇒ A` is one-sided representable if and only if it admits a cut-free de