 prove that on precisely this class the full calculus and the corresponding one-sided fragment have the same derivable sequents.', 'statement_prelude_code': '', 'formalized_stmt': '∀ (Γ : List Tp) (A : Tp), (LeftRep Γ A ∨ RightRep Γ A) ↔ (Γ ⇒ A ∧ ((∀ x ∈ A :: Γ, LeftDivisionOnly x) ∨ (∀ x ∈ A :: Γ, RightDivisionOnly x)))', 'prelude_code': "lemma exists_left_ctx_of_left_only (Γ : List Tp) (hΓ : ∀ x ∈ Γ, LeftDivisionOnly x) :\n    ∃ Γ' : List Left.Tp, Left.ctxToProductFree Γ' = Γ := by\n  induction Γ with\n  | nil =>\n      exact ⟨[], rfl⟩\n  | cons A Γ ih =>\n      have hA : LeftDivisionOnly A := hΓ A (by simp)\n      have htail : ∀ x ∈ Γ, LeftDivisionOnly x := by\n        intro x hx\n        exact hΓ x (by simp [hx])\n      rcases exists_left_tp_of_left_only hA with ⟨A', hA'⟩\n      rcases ih htail with ⟨Γ', hΓ'⟩\n      refine ⟨A' :: Γ', ?_⟩\n      simpa [Left.ctxToProductFree, hA'] using congrArg (List.cons A'.toProductFree) hΓ'\n\nlemma exists_right_ctx_of_right_only (Γ : List Tp) (hΓ : ∀ x ∈ Γ, RightDivisionOnly x) :\n    ∃ Γ' : List Right.Tp, Right.ctxToProductFree Γ' = Γ := by\n  induction Γ with\n  | nil =>\n      exact ⟨[], rfl⟩\n  | cons A Γ ih =>\n      have hA : RightDivisionOnly A := hΓ A (by simp)\n      have htail : ∀ x ∈ Γ, RightDivisionOnly x := by\n        intro x hx\n        exact hΓ x (by simp [hx])\n      rcases exists_right_tp_of_right_only hA with ⟨A', hA'⟩\n      rcases ih htail with ⟨Γ', hΓ'⟩\n      refine ⟨A' :: Γ', ?_⟩\n      simpa [Right.ctxToProductFree, hA'] using congrArg (List.cons A'.toProductFree) hΓ'", 'prover_statement_result': 'ok', 'prover_attempts_used': 1, 'priority_refresh_ran': True, 'priority_refresh_error': '', 'expand_candidates': [{'statement': '∀ (Γ : List Tp) (A : Tp), (LeftRep Γ A ∧ RightRep Γ A) ↔ (Γ ⇒ A ∧ ∀ x ∈ A :: Γ, is_atom x)', 'rationale': 'The solved theorem identifies the union of the one-sided fragments by uniform orientation. The next sharp boundary is their overlap: this candidate would show that simultaneous left- and right-fragment representability happens exactly in the atomic regime, giving a genuine separation/intersection theorem rather than another local transport lemma.'}, {'statement': '∀ (Γ : List Tp) (A : Tp), Γ ⇒ A → ((¬ LeftRep Γ A ∧ ¬ RightRep Γ A) ↔ (¬ (∀ x ∈ A :: Γ, LeftDivisionOnly x) ∧ ¬ (∀ x ∈ A :: Γ, RightDivisionOnly x)))', 'rationale': 'This is the strict complement of the new classification and turns the solved equivalence into an explicit non-representability criterion. It matters because it isolates the exact obstruction to fragment collapse for arbitrary sequents, making the separation from the one-sided subsystems usable as a theorem rather than only as a contrapositive reading of the solved result.'}, {'statement': '∀ {Γ : List Tp} {A : Tp}, LeftRep Γ A → RightRep Γ A → ∃ s : String, Γ = [Tp.atom s] ∧ A = Tp.atom s', 'rationale': 'A singleton-atomic rigidity theorem would sharpen the overlap boundary to its minimal derivable core and connect the new arbitrary-sequent fragment criterion to the verified singleton-atom theorem already present in the theory. This is not peripheral because it converts fragment overlap into a strong rigidity principle, clarifying that the two one-sided calculi coincide only at the atomic axiom boundary.'}], 'stored_expand_rows': [{'id': 'op_000043', 'stmt': '∀ (Γ : List Tp) (A : Tp), (LeftRep Γ A ∧ RightRep Γ A) ↔ (Γ ⇒ A ∧ ∀ x ∈ A :: Γ, is_atom x)', 'src': 'expand', 'mode': 'expand_candidate', 'summary_delta': 'The solved theorem identifies the union of the one-sided fragments by uniform orientation. The next sharp boundary is their overlap: this candidate would show that simultaneous left- and right-fragment representability happens exactly in the atomic regime, giving a genuine separation/intersection theorem rather than another local transport lemma.', 'source_kind': 'expand_candidate', 'generated_from_source_id': 'op_000041', 'generated_from_source_kind': 'open_problem', 'priority': 'unknown', 'priority_ration